[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Mena-asia_default_banner.jpg"]]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Koriyama"]}," is a city in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Fukushima (prefecture)"],["Fukushima"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Japan"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n\nKoriyama is the largest city in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Fukushima (prefecture)"],["Fukushima Prefecture"]]}," and has good rail, road and bus networks linking it to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Tokyo"]]}," in the south and other parts of Tohoku to the north and west.\n\nThe ",{"type":"'''","value":["Tohoku Shinkansen"]}," is the fastest way to get to and from Tokyo (80 minutes, ￥7970), as well as other major cities in Tohoku, such as ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Fukushima"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Sendai"]]}," (40 minutes, ￥5240).\n\nThe ",{"type":"'''","value":["Tohoku Main Line"]}," follows a similar route to the Shinkansen, and though cheaper, it is much slower and trains run far less regularly.\n\nThe ",{"type":"'''","value":["West Ban'etsu Line"]}," connects Koriyama with ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Niigata"]]}," in the west, travelling via the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mount Bandai"]]}," region.\n\nThere are also buses linking Koriyama with Tokyo and Narita Airport.\n\nKoriyama is situated on the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Tohoku Expressway"]},", with interchanges at Koriyama and Koriyama Minami.\n\nThe nearest airport, ",{"type":"'''","value":["Fukushima Airport"]},", is in Sukagawa city, about 20km to the south. Fukushima Airport has daily flights to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Okinawa"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Osaka"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Sapporo"]]},", with less frequent international flights to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Seoul"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Shanghai"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Buy"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat